get_water_surface_light
Disk World creator help
get_water_surface_light

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
get_water_surface_light -  This function returns the amount of light that will filter down to this room from those above it if set_use_surface_light has been called.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
int get_water_surface_light()
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
the amount of light that filters down from rooms above this one.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/basic/water.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This function returns the amount of light that will filter down to this
room from those above it if set_use_surface_light has been called.  It is
intended to be used only by the update_water_light function, but has been
separated out to allow it to be masked.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
update_water_light, query_above_room, query_water_surface_light

.EP

